  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 14 airports right now. Engine anti-ice operations are flagged at Sandefjord Airport, Torp (TRF/ENTO), Suceava Stefan cel Mare (SCV/LRSV). Across base airports: 4 critical, 10 high, 10 medium, 15 normal. Key bases needing attention include London Luton (LTN/EGGW), Chişinău (RMO/LUKK) and Iaşi (IAS/LRIA); plus 11 other bases. 10 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is mist, low cloud base and cold‑temperature performance penalties  — most notably around Suceava Stefan cel Mare (SCV/LRSV), Venice Marco Polo (VCE/LIPZ) and Craiova (CRA/LRCV). Network hotspots: Sandefjord Airport, Torp (TRF/ENTO), Suceava Stefan cel Mare (SCV/LRSV), Treviso Antonio Canova (TSF/LIPH), Trieste–Friuli Venezia Giulia (TRS/LIPQ), Venice Marco Polo (VCE/LIPZ) and 9 others. Primary drivers: low cloud base, RVR limitations and very low visibility. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Sandefjord Airport, Torp (TRF/ENTO), Treviso Antonio Canova (TSF/LIPH), Trieste–Friuli Venezia Giulia (TRS/LIPQ) and 9 others.",
